An alternative translation of the ''eorðan'' and ''aelda'' texts, however, understands ''weorc'' as the subject: &quot;Now the works of the father of glory must honour the guardian of heaven, the might of the architect, and his mind's purpose&quot;. See [[#mitchell1985|Mitchell 1985]], [[#ball1985|Ball 1985]], pp. 39&amp;ndash;41, and [[#howlett1974|Howlett 1974]], p. 6.&lt;/ref&gt; — as he the beginning of wonders
